post_text: Kindergarten Preview – Do you have a child entering kindergarten this year? We would love for your child to join us at our Kindergarten Preview. It will be one day, two hours, and will help your child get a feel for what the first day of kindergarten will be like. Your child will get a tour of the campus with Ms. Tiger, one of our Kindergarten teachers, meet some new friends, and get to experience the classroom. The following dates are available: Monday 6/22 8am – 10pm, Wednesday 6/24 10am – 12:00pm, and Friday 6/26 1PM – 3PM. Please contact Ms. Staggie - jstaggie@hveast.com for additional information and to reserve your spot. Kindergarten preview is not just for Happy Valley students; any student starting kindergarten next year is welcome to attend. So, bring a friend or pass this information on to someone you know.

Meet the teacher is Wednesday, July 17th from Noon to 6pm. Swing on by and say hi and meet your child's teacher.

Start in the cafeteria and sign up for the booster club and parent volunteer groups. Information regarding lunches, transportation, parent pick up, scouts, uniforms, and before and after care will be available as well.

Need uniforms? Used uniforms shirts and bottoms will be available for purchase. Can't wait to see you all there.

Thank you to the Kiwanis Club of Queen Creek “Members of the Kiwanis Club of Queen Creek have recently distributed ‘free dictionaries’ to all the 3rd graders at our school. The Kiwanis Club will distribute over 3,000 ‘free dictionaries’ to area 3rd graders in over 30 local elementary schools. The revenues needed to purchase these dictionaries, in part, is derived from you donating serviceable used clothing into the Kiwanis/Big Brothers Big Sisters of Arizona clothing donation box located outside of the school. They will accept clothing, linens, shoes, belts, purses, draperies, blankets and the like donations.”
http://hvseast.com/3rd-grade-dictionaries/

post_text: It has been a wonderful and exciting first day of school. It has been great seeing all the students happy faces. As we approach the end of our first day of school, please remember to be extra courteous and patient for the first few days during student drop off and pick up. The lines are always a little longer and slower while everyone is getting used to the process. Please keep in mind that buses might be delayed or running a little late, as students get used to their dismissal and bus routines. We want everyone to have a great experience and to be safe. Remember to stay hydrated. Drink lots of water and stay cool. It's a hot one.

*** Teachers Needed for Grades K-6 *** (San Tan Valley)

For the 2016-2017 School Year

Qualifications:
*Must have a Bachelor’s Degree
*Be highly qualified (have taken the NES or AEPA)
*SEI Endorsement is a plus

Our school offers competitive salaries and a full complement of benefits which include medical/dental/vision insurance, short-term disability, life insurance and a 401K with a 4% company match.

Application Instructions:
*Please send resume, copy of fingerprint clearance card, certification information, and AEPA or NES passing scores. We will call you for an interview if deemed a good fit.
lokonowski@hveast.com.

Happy Valley School East Campus is an equal Employment Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status
